        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 7:38PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 738 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Stamps, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stamps, Lewisville, Buckner, Rosston, Willisville, Bodcaw, Bluff
City, Cale, Patmos, Mount Moriah, Waterloo, Laneburg, Falcon,
Sutton, Morris, Young and Piney Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
